er, a national identity card or passport is compulsory for German citizens aged 16 or over, and valid identity documentation is compulsory for other EEA citizens\n|\n* \u20ac28.80 (applicants aged 24 or over)\n* \u20ac22.80 (applicants aged under 24)\n|\n* 10 years (applicants aged 24 or over)\n* 6 years (applicants aged under 24)\n|\n* City or town of residence\n* German embassy in country of residence (for German citizens living abroad)\n| 1 November 2010\n|-\n| style=\"height:100px\" | {{flagicon|Gibraltar}}<br />[[Gibraltar identity card|Gibraltar]]<br />(United Kingdom)\n|\n| \n| style=\"background:#B7FFAD\" | Identity documentation is optional\n| Free of charge\n|\n* 10 years (adults aged 16 or over)\n* 5 years (children under 16)\n| Civil Status and Registration Office, Gibraltar, U.K.\n| 8 December 2000\n|-\n| style=\"height:100px\" | {{flagicon|Greece}}<br />[[Greek identity card|Greece]]\n| [[File:Greek ID Card-Front.jpg|180x180px|alt=]]\n| [[File:Greek_ID_Card-Back.jpg|180x180px|alt=]]\n| style=\"background:#FFADB7\" | National identity card compulsory for Greek citizens aged 12 or over\n|\n* Free of charge for first issue\n* \u20ac9 for reissue if lost or destroyed (free if reported stolen)\n| 15 years\n| Police\n| 1 July 2010\n|-\n| style=\"height:100px\" | {{flagicon|Hungary}}<br />[[Hungarian identity card|Hungary]]<br />[[File:EPassport logo.svg|20px]]\n| [[File:HunIDfront.jpg|180x180px|alt=]]\n| [[File:HunIDback.jpg|180x180px|alt=]]\n| style=\"background:#FFFFBB\" | National identity card optional; however, a national identity card, passport or driving licence is compulsory for Hungarian citizens aged 14\n|\n* Free of charge\n| \n* 60 years (adults aged 65 or over)\n* 6 years (adults aged over 18)\n* 3 years (children under 18, but only until the date on which the holder reaches the age of 12)\n|\n| 1 January 2016\n|-\n| style=\"height:100px\" | {{flagicon|Iceland}}<br />Iceland\n| colspan=\"2\" |No national identity card. Icelandic state-issued ide